        "plantName": {
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "which plant — completes the row label, one line, truncates with ellipsis"
        },
        "status": {
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "enum": [
            "ok",
            "due",
            "overdue"
          ],
          "description": "task urgency — rendered by the status-chip child, drives the due/overdue states"
        },
        "checked": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "required": false,
          "description": "marked-done in this session, awaiting the log-care commit; defaults to false"
        }
      },
      "tokens": [
        "--color-bg-surface",
        "--color-fg",
        "--color-fg-muted",
        "--color-border",
        "--color-accent",
        "--radius-md",
        "--spacing-sm",
        "--spacing-md",
        "--type-body"
      ],
      "states": [
        "default",
        "due",
        "overdue",
        "checked"
      ],
      "children": [
        "status-chip"
      ],
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "Usage",
          "body": "Component of the Verdant demo scenario (fictional product). One row of the \"Today\" list: a scheduled care action for one plant — check circle left, \"Water Monstera\" label centre, status-chip right. Use only in the today list between the stat-tiles and the primary-button; tapping anywhere on the row toggles `checked` (the primary-button commits the batch). One action per row — a plant needing water and fertiliser is two rows, not a compound row."
        },
        {
          "title": "States",
          "body": "- **default** — `status: \"ok\"`: scheduled but not urgent; empty check circle in `--color-border`, chip in its ok variant.\n- **due** — `status: \"due\"`: chip in its due variant; the row itself does not recolour (the chip carries the signal, same rule as plant-card).\n- **overdue** — `status: \"overdue\"`: chip in its overdue variant; the check circle's ring moves to `--color-accent` — the row's one escalation.\n- **checked** — `checked: true`: circle fills `--color-accent`, label softens to `--color-fg-muted`; the chip stays as-is (urgency is fact until the log commits)."
        },
        {
          "title": "Data binding",
          "body": "Renders one `CareTask` record (care-task-row.contract.json). Mapping:\n\n| Contract field | Element | When absent |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `type` | leading verb of the label (`--type-body`, `--color-fg`) | required — never absent |\n| `plantName` | rest of the label — denormalised, the row never fetches the plant | required — never absent |\n| `status` | status-chip child | required — never absent |\n| `id` | `data-task-id` attribute (what the log-care commit sends) | required — never absent |\n| `plantId` | not rendered — join key for the API, kept off the DOM | required — never absent |\n| `due` | not rendered — the \"Today\" grouping already says when | required — never absent |\n| `done` | not rendered — history fact; done tasks stay out of the Today list | required — never absent |\n\nSample record (valid against the contract — a real record from the mock API):\n\n```json\n{ \"id\": \"task-03\", \"plantId\": \"plant-03\", \"plantName\": \"Fiddle-leaf fig\", \"type\": \"water\", \"due\": \"2026-07-12\", \"done\": false, \"status\": \"overdue\" }\n```"
        },
        {
          "title": "Accessibility",
          "body": "The row is a `<button role=\"checkbox\">` with `aria-checked` mirroring `checked`; accessible name = action + plant + status (\"Water Monstera, due\"), chip text `aria-hidden` against double announcement. Whole row is the target, minimum 44px tall; visible `:focus-visible` outline in `--color-accent`; checked state is carried by the filled circle plus `aria-checked`, never colour alone."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "component": "demo-notice",
      "status": "spec",
      "class": "vd-demo-notice",
      "contract": null,
      "props": {
        "text": {
          "type": "string",
          "required": true,
          "description": "the scenario's fictionalNotice string, rendered verbatim — never paraphrased or summarized"
