      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "Usage",
          "body": "Component of the Verdant demo scenario (fictional product). The phone app bar: back affordance left, screen title centre, settings right — always the topmost element of a screen, exactly one per screen. Presentational: it renders what the composing screen passes, it fetches nothing and owns no state beyond scroll elevation. Keep the title short enough to never truncate (\"My plants\", not a sentence)."
        },
        {
          "title": "States",
          "body": "- **default** — at scroll top: `--color-bg` fill, no bottom rule; the bar and the content read as one surface.\n- **scrolled** — content has scrolled beneath: a `--color-border` hairline appears at the bottom edge. No shadow, no blur — one hairline is the whole elevation story."
        },
        {
          "title": "Data binding",
          "body": "Presentational — `contract: null`. No API record binds here; the composing screen sets the props. Mapping:\n\n| Prop | Element | When absent |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `title` | centre text (`--type-h3`, `--color-fg`) | required — never absent |\n| `showBack` | leading chevron affordance | slot left empty, title stays centred |\n| `showSettings` | trailing gear affordance | slot left empty, title stays centred |"
