          "body": "A `<header>` landmark; the title is the screen's top-level heading within its frame — when the screen is embedded in a page that owns the `<h1>` (like the prototype exhibit), the title steps down to the next level. Back and settings are `<button>`s with explicit labels (\"Back\", \"Settings\") — the glyphs are `aria-hidden`. Both targets minimum 44px with visible `:focus-visible` outlines; the empty-slot rule keeps the title from shifting when affordances toggle, so nothing moves under a screen-reader user's touch."
