      ],
      "states": [
        "ok",
        "due",
        "overdue"
      ],
      "children": [],
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "Usage",
          "body": "Component of the Verdant demo scenario (fictional product). The one categorical state signal of the system: a small pill naming a plant's care state. Always a child — of a plant-card or a care-task-row, trailing edge — never free-standing, never a tap target. One chip per parent (the parent summarises one state); if two states compete, the parent's data is wrong, not the chip."
        },
        {
          "title": "States",
          "body": "The three states are the three data variants — the chip has no interaction states of its own:\n\n- **ok** — quiet: `--color-fg-muted` text on `--color-bg-surface`, `--color-border` hairline. Recedes; the list should scan calm when nothing is due.\n- **due** — signal: `--color-accent` text and border on `--color-bg-surface`. Advances without shouting.\n- **overdue** — escalated: solid `--color-accent` fill, `--color-accent-fg` text. The only filled variant — reserved so it stays loud."
        },
        {
          "title": "Data binding",
          "body": "Renders one `Status` record (status-chip.contract.json). When composed inside plant-card or care-task-row, the parent derives the record from its own `status` field (value → canonical label, e.g. `\"due\"` → `\"DUE\"`). Mapping:\n\n| Contract field | Element | When absent |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `value` | variant class on the pill (`ok` / `due` / `overdue`) | required — never absent |\n| `label` | the pill text (`--type-eyebrow`, uppercase) | required — never absent |\n\nSample record (valid against the contract):\n\n```json\n{ \"value\": \"overdue\", \"label\": \"3 DAYS OVERDUE\" }\n```"
        },
        {
          "title": "Accessibility",
          "body": "Text in a `<span>` — no role, no tabindex (the chip is never interactive). When the parent already speaks the state in its accessible name (plant-card does), the chip is `aria-hidden` to avoid double announcement; free label text plus the variant means state never relies on colour alone. Minimum `--type-eyebrow` size with generous letter-spacing keeps the uppercase legible."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
