          "type": "boolean",
          "required": false,
          "description": "marked-done in this session, awaiting the log-care commit; defaults to false"
        }
      },
      "states": [
        "default",
        "due",
        "overdue",
        "checked"
      ],
      "children": [
        "status-chip"
      ],
      "usage": "Component of the Verdant demo scenario (fictional product). One row of the \"Today\" list: a scheduled care action for one plant — check circle left, \"Water Monstera\" label centre, status-chip right. Use only in the today list between the stat-tiles and the primary-button; tapping anywhere on the row toggles `checked` (the primary-button commits the batch). One action per row — a plant needing water and fertiliser is two rows, not a compound row.",
